# ============================================================
# .cursorrules — AtomQuest 1.0 Goal-Tracking Portal
# ============================================================

## PROJECT IDENTITY
This is AtomQuest 1.0: a Next.js 14 (App Router) + Supabase
Goal Setting & Tracking Portal for an HR hackathon.
Stack: Next.js 14, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui,
Supabase (Auth + Postgres + Realtime), React Hook Form + Zod,
Zustand, React Query (TanStack Query v5), SheetJS (xlsx).

## CODING STANDARDS
- TypeScript strict mode. No 'any'. All types explicitly declared.
- Functional components only. No class components.
- All async Server Actions must be in /app/actions/*.ts files.
- API routes only for webhooks; all other mutations via Server Actions.
- Use 'use client' directive only at leaf components that need state/events.
- Always colocate component, test, and story in same folder.
- File naming: PascalCase for components, kebab-case for routes.
- Use path aliases: @/components, @/lib, @/types, @/hooks.
- Export named exports only; no default exports except Next.js pages/layouts.
- Never use inline styles. Always Tailwind utility classes or CSS variables.

## VALIDATION RULES — CRITICAL
These rules must be enforced at BOTH the frontend (Zod schema) and
backend (Server Action + Postgres constraint). Never enforce only one layer.

const GOAL_SHEET_RULES = {
  MAX_GOALS: 8,
  MIN_WEIGHTAGE_PER_GOAL: 10,  // percent
  TOTAL_WEIGHTAGE: 100,         // must equal exactly
  UOM_TYPES: ['numeric_min', 'numeric_max', 'timeline', 'zero'],
} as const;

Zod schema for a single goal:
const goalSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(3).max(200),
  thrust_area: z.string().min(1),
  uom_type: z.enum(['numeric_min','numeric_max','timeline','zero']),
  target_value: z.number().positive().nullable(),
  target_date: z.string().date().nullable(),
  weightage: z.number().min(10).max(100),
  description: z.string().max(500).optional(),
});

Zod refine for the full sheet:
.refine(goals => goals.reduce((s,g) => s + g.weightage, 0) === 100,
  { message: 'Total weightage must equal 100%' })
.refine(goals => goals.length <= 8,
  { message: 'Maximum 8 goals per sheet' })

## LOCKING MECHANISM
- goal_sheets.is_locked (boolean) is the single source of truth.
- Set is_locked = true atomically inside the approveGoalSheet() Server Action
  using a Supabase transaction (rpc call wrapping both the status update and lock).
- Every Server Action that mutates goal/sheet fields MUST begin with:
  const { is_locked } = await getGoalSheetLockStatus(sheetId);
  if (is_locked) throw new Error('SHEET_LOCKED');
- The UI must reflect locked state: render all goal fields as <span> not <input>.
- Add a LockBadge component (padlock icon + 'Approved & Locked' text) to locked sheets.

## SHARED GOALS — SYNC LOGIC
Shared Goals connect a primary owner's goal row to N recipient goal rows
via the shared_goal_links junction table.

PUSH FLOW (Admin/Manager):
1. Admin calls pushSharedGoal(sourceGoalId, recipientEmployeeIds[]).
2. Server Action creates a goal row (is_shared=true) in each recipient's goal_sheet
   copying title, thrust_area, uom_type, target_value, target_date from source.
3. Insert shared_goal_links rows linking source → each target.
4. Recipients can only edit weightage on their copy.

ACHIEVEMENT SYNC FLOW:
When the primary owner logs a check-in (actual achievement):
1. checkins row is inserted/updated for source_goal_id.
2. A Postgres trigger (after_checkin_upsert) fires:
   - Reads all shared_goal_links where source_goal_id = NEW.goal_id.
   - Inserts/upserts identical checkin rows for each target_goal_id,
     preserving the recipient's own manager_comment.
3. Supabase Realtime broadcasts on channel 'shared-goal-{sourceGoalId}'.
4. Frontend subscribes to this channel and invalidates React Query cache
   for the affected goal sheets to trigger UI refresh.

RECIPIENT CONSTRAINT:
- On the recipient's goal row: title, uom_type, target_value, target_date
  are all read-only. Enforce in UI and in Server Action (throw if attempted).
- Only weightage is mutable by the recipient.

## AUDIT TRAIL — POST-LOCK CHANGES
All mutations to goals or goal_sheets after lock must be captured.

Implementation:
1. Create Postgres function log_goal_change() as a trigger function.
2. Attach as AFTER UPDATE trigger on goals and goal_sheets tables.
3. Function body inserts into audit_log:
   INSERT INTO audit_log(goal_sheet_id, goal_id, actor_id, action,
     field_changed, old_value, new_value, changed_at)
   SELECT NEW.goal_sheet_id, NEW.id, current_setting('app.current_user_id'),
     'UPDATE', column_name, old_val::text, new_val::text, now()
   FROM jsonb_each_text(to_jsonb(OLD)) AS old_vals(column_name, old_val)
   JOIN jsonb_each_text(to_jsonb(NEW)) AS new_vals(column_name, new_val)
     USING (column_name)
   WHERE old_val IS DISTINCT FROM new_val;

4. Set actor context before each mutation in Server Action:
   await supabaseAdmin.rpc('set_config', {
     parameter: 'app.current_user_id', value: session.user.id, is_local: true
   });

5. Admin UI: /app/admin/audit-log/page.tsx — filterable table showing all
   audit_log rows with columns: Time | Actor | Sheet | Goal | Field | Old | New.

## QUARTERLY WINDOW ENFORCEMENT
- Active window is determined server-side from the cycles table.
- Helper: getCurrentWindow() → 'goal_setting' | 'Q1' | 'Q2' | 'Q3' | 'Q4' | null
- Every check-in Server Action calls getCurrentWindow() first.
  If result is null or doesn't match expected quarter → return { error: 'WINDOW_CLOSED' }.
- Never trust the client's date. All window checks are server-side only.
- UI: Render a <WindowStatusBanner /> at layout level (layout.tsx) so it appears
  on every page. Feed it a server-fetched prop — not a client-side Date.now().

## PROGRESS SCORE COMPUTATION
Scores are computed in Postgres via compute_progress_score() function.
Call it inside the checkin upsert trigger, not in application code.
Never expose raw formula computation in frontend JavaScript —
the score column on checkins is the single source of truth.

## ROLES & RLS
Supabase RLS policies:
- employee: SELECT own goal_sheet only; INSERT/UPDATE own goals pre-lock; INSERT checkins in open window.
- manager: SELECT all goal_sheets for their direct reports; UPDATE during approval; INSERT manager_comment.
- admin: Full SELECT; UPDATE is_locked; INSERT into audit_log for unlock reasons; manage cycles.
Role is stored in users.role. Always join through users table — never trust client-supplied role claims.

## ERROR HANDLING CONVENTIONS
- Server Actions return { data, error } — never throw to client.
- Error codes (string enum): SHEET_LOCKED | WINDOW_CLOSED | VALIDATION_FAILED |
  MAX_GOALS_REACHED | UNAUTHORISED | NOT_FOUND
- Frontend: useActionState hook wraps all form submissions.
- Toast notifications for success/error using sonner library.

## COMPONENT LIBRARY CONVENTIONS
- Use shadcn/ui primitives (Button, Dialog, Table, Badge, Select).
- Extend with project-specific components in @/components/ui/.
- Key custom components to build first:
  GoalCard | ValidationBanner | ProgressGauge | WindowStatusBanner |
  LockBadge | SharedGoalBadge | CheckinRow | AuditLogTable | RoleSwitcher

## FILE STRUCTURE
/app
  /(auth)/login/page.tsx
  /(employee)/goal-sheet/page.tsx
  /(employee)/checkins/page.tsx
  /(manager)/team/page.tsx
  /(manager)/approvals/[sheetId]/page.tsx
  /(admin)/cycles/page.tsx
  /(admin)/audit-log/page.tsx
  /(admin)/reports/page.tsx
  /actions/goals.ts
  /actions/checkins.ts
  /actions/admin.ts
/components
  /ui/  (shadcn + custom)
  /goals/
  /checkins/
  /admin/
/lib
  /supabase/  (client.ts, server.ts, admin.ts)
  /validations/  (goal-schema.ts, checkin-schema.ts)
  /utils/  (window.ts, progress.ts, export.ts)
/types
  /database.types.ts  (generated from Supabase)
  /app.types.ts

## DO NOT
- Do NOT put business logic in React components. Move to Server Actions or lib/.
- Do NOT use useEffect for data fetching. Use React Query or Server Components.
- Do NOT hardcode dates for window enforcement. Always read from cycles table.
- Do NOT allow mutations on audit_log from the application layer.
- Do NOT render achievement input fields without checking window status first.
- Do NOT compute progress scores in JavaScript. Always use the Postgres function.
# ============================================================
